        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nVTP captures the errors/ouputs for every execution instance and why do this change required?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "e33498a78ee46c30b1840a388e7d3c51884d090d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5098,
          "name": "Bartosz Gardziejewski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bartosz.gardziejewski@nokia.com",
          "username": "BartoszG"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-09 10:40:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> VTP captures the errors/ouputs for every execution instance and why do this change required?\n\nYes, output is captured and saved in right file during validation for every execution instance, when POST with correct data is called, however once we want to retrieve result data after that, the GET method is always returning empty result object. This change is fixing that, by adding execution result data to GET response",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
